1. *Prljava* odeća može izazvati iritaciju kože. (Dirty clothing can cause skin irritation.)
2. Nikada ne bih mogao da živim u *prljavoj* kući. (I could never live in a dirty house.)
3. Molim te, operi te *prljave* tanjire pre nego što večeramo. (Please wash those dirty dishes before we have dinner.)
4. Izgleda da je ona jedina koja ne primećuje koliko su joj ruke *prljave*. (It seems like she is the only one who doesn't notice how dirty her hands are.)
5. Kada smo se vratili s pecanja, bili smo *prljavi* do kolena. (When we came back from fishing, we were dirty up to our knees.)
6. Moramo očistiti *prljavi* pod pre nego što gosti dođu. (We need to clean the dirty floor before the guests arrive.)
7. *Prljave* ruke su odličan način da se prenesu bakterije. (Dirty hands are a great way to transfer bacteria.)
8. Ona ima naviku da ostavlja *prljave* tanjire u sudoperi danima. (She has a habit of leaving dirty dishes in the sink for days.)
9. Čišćenje *prljavog* prozora može biti jako naporno. (Cleaning a dirty window can be very exhausting.)
10. On nikada ne pere svoje *prljave* čarape, samo ih baci i kupi nove. (He never washes his dirty socks, he just throws them away and buys new ones.)